@startuml domain-result-artifacts
title SafeCrowd Domain Result Artifacts

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "domain" {
  abstract class PersistedArtifact {
    artifactId
    schema version
    created at
  }

  class RunResult {
    runId
    status
    seed
    variation key
  }

  class RunMetadata {
    scenario id
    execution config
    started / finished at
  }

  class MetricSummary {
    total evac time
    percentile evac time
    max density
    hotspot counts
  }

  class DoorHistory {
    time series
    throughput
    queue
  }

  class RoomHistory {
    time series
    density
    congestion
  }

  class MeasurementRegionSeries {
    region id
    sampled metrics
  }

  class OccupantHistory {
    occupant trace
    optional detail
  }

  class ArtifactIndex {
    storage keys
    export manifest
  }

  class VariationSummary {
    variation key
    aggregate metrics
  }

  class ScenarioComparison {
    baseline vs alternatives
    delta metrics
  }

  class CumulativeArtifact {
    canonical summary
    export-ready bundle
  }
}

PersistedArtifact <|-- RunResult
PersistedArtifact <|-- VariationSummary
PersistedArtifact <|-- ScenarioComparison
PersistedArtifact <|-- CumulativeArtifact

RunResult *-- RunMetadata
RunResult *-- MetricSummary
RunResult o-- DoorHistory
RunResult o-- RoomHistory
RunResult o-- MeasurementRegionSeries
RunResult o-- OccupantHistory : optional
RunResult --> ArtifactIndex : raw artifact references

VariationSummary --> RunResult : aggregates persisted runs
VariationSummary *-- MetricSummary : aggregate
ScenarioComparison --> VariationSummary : baseline + alternatives
CumulativeArtifact --> VariationSummary : summary bundle
CumulativeArtifact --> ScenarioComparison : comparison payload
CumulativeArtifact --> ArtifactIndex : canonical export references

note bottom of RunResult
  Run result is the smallest persisted execution unit.
  It may exist even when a higher-level variation or
  comparison summary has not been computed yet.
end note

note bottom of VariationSummary
  Variation summary aggregates repeated runs
  and keeps Monte Carlo style statistics separate
  from a single deterministic run output.
end note

note bottom of ScenarioComparison
  ScenarioComparison is also a persisted artifact.
  It is not a screen-only delta view rebuilt
  ad hoc every time the user opens comparison.
end note

note bottom of OccupantHistory
  Occupant history is optional by design.
  The core result pipeline should remain valid
  even when detailed per-occupant traces are disabled.
end note

note bottom of CumulativeArtifact
  Cumulative artifact is the canonical bundle
  used by export, comparison, and recommendation input.
  It references persisted summaries and histories
  rather than duplicating every raw sample.
end note

note bottom of PersistedArtifact
  Repository-managed result objects share
  stable identity and schema versioning
  so downstream workflows can reload them safely.
end note

@enduml
